    "description": "A version of MagicMock for multithreading tests. The ThreadingMock object provides extra methods to wait for a call to be invoked, rather than assert on it immediately. The default timeout is specified by the timeout argument, or if unset by the ThreadingMock.DEFAULT_TIMEOUT attribute, which defaults to blocking (None). You can configure the global default timeout by setting ThreadingMock.DEFAULT_TIMEOUT. wait_until_called(*, timeout=UNSET)¶ Waits until the mock is called. If a timeout was pa...",
